---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="The story behind Rise & Grain bakery — quality, community, sustainability.">
  <section class="about-hero content-column">
    <h1>Our Story</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Rise &amp; Grain started the way most good things do — with a question that
      wouldn't leave us alone. What would happen if we slowed everything down?
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="story content-column">
    <p>
      In 2018, Maya Chen left her job at a Portland tech company and started baking
      in a converted garage with a single deck oven and fifty pounds of locally
      milled flour. The first loaves went to neighbors. Then farmers' market regulars.
      Then a line started forming before the garage door even rolled up.
    </p>
    <p>
      Today, Rise &amp; Grain occupies a sun-filled corner shop on Division Street,
      but the process hasn't changed. Every loaf is hand-shaped. Every batch of flour
      is sourced from farms within a hundred miles. We don't rush fermentation, and
      we don't cut corners on ingredients. The bread takes as long as it takes — and
      you can taste the difference.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="values content-column">
    <h2 class="section-title">What We Stand For</h2>
    <div class="values-grid">
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Quality</h3>
        <p>
          Long fermentation, stone-milled flour, and no shortcuts. We'd rather bake
          fewer loaves than compromise on a single one.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Community</h3>
        <p>
          Bread has always been communal. Our baking classes, bread shares, and open
          kitchen keep that tradition alive.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-card">
        <h3>Sustainability</h3>
        <p>
          Oregon-grown grain, compostable packaging, and a zero-waste kitchen. The
          land feeds us — we take care of it in return.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .story {
    padding-top: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .story p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .values {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .value-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--secondary);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .value-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
    }

    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
